        "description": "* WHAT...South winds 35 to 45 mph, with gusts up to 60 to 75 mph\nexpected.\n\n* WHERE...Unalaska and Nikolski.\n\n* WHEN...Until 4 PM AKDT this afternoon.\n\n* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and a few\npower outages may result.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong southerly winds will continue through\nSunday morning. For Unalaska, gusts of up to 65 mph are expected.\nFor Nikolski, gusts of up to 75 mph are expected. Winds will slowly\ndecrease this afternoon and evening.",
        "severity": "Moderate",
        "certainty": "Likely",
        "urgency": "Expected",
        "sender": "NWS Anchorage AK",
        "effective": "2026-04-26T01:56:00-08:00",
        "expires": "2026-04-26T16:00:00-08:00",
        "areas": "Unalaska and Nikolski",
        "category": "Met",
        "response": "Execute",
        "instruction": "People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around\nor damaged by the wind. Use caution if traveling.",
